x4freetext: Self-supporting B-11 foil of 0.275 mg/cm**2 thickness
150 cm diameter scattering chamber equipped
with 4 dE-E telescopes. Each telescope consisted of
two independent dE sections and a common E section.
In this way, one telescope could measure at two
different angles.
The beam intensity was about
20 particles / nA. Before the measurement an additional
beam monochromatization was carried out to improve the
beam energy spreading.
The data were analyzed by the statistical compound
nucleus model and the coupled-reaction channels
method for direct neutron transfer.

asymptotic normalization coefficients and rms radii
